After Miami Ink ended, James moved to New York City in 2011 to fulfill his dream of opening a tattoo studio which he named the Wooster St. Social Club. 
He was joined again by producers David Roma and Charlie Corwin to detail the proceedings in the shop on NY Ink. The series follows the events of the tattoo artist Ami James and his new shop, the Wooster St. Social Club tattoo studio in New York City, New York.
